window.bookSummaryJSON = "Somewhere in New England, nine-year-old Trisha gets lost in the woods while on a walk with her family. Her only comforts are the radio broadcasts of Boston Red Sox games featuring her favorite player, closing pitcher Tom Gordon. Lonely, frightened, starving, and cold, Gordon becomes Trisha's imaginary companion - and the key to her survival against an unidentified someone (or some <i>thing</i>) leaving death and destruction in its wake. <p><br><br><br><i>The Girl Who Loved Tom Gordon</i> is read by celebrated actress Anne Heche, star of numerous major motion pictures including <i>Return to Paradise</i> and <i>Wag the Dog</i>.</p>"; 
